 \dfrac{\partial (x'Ax)}{\partial x} = x'(A'+A)
x_k
 x'Ax = \sum_{j=1}^n \sum_{i=1}^n a_{ij}x_ix_j
\dfrac{\partial (x'Ax)}{\partial x_k}= \sum_{j=1}^n a_{kj}x_j + \sum_{i=1}^n a_{ik}x_i\ ;  \forall k = 1,...,n
\dfrac{\partial (x'Ax)}{\partial x} = x'A'+x'A
